It's a cron
Usage:
crontab
options:
	-l -> list of task
	-e -> edit task
How to add task
$ crontab
M H DM M DW /bin/execute/this/script.sh
------------------------------------
M - minute (from 0 to 59)
H - hour (from 0 to 23)
DM - day of month (from 1 to 31)
M - month (from 1 to 12)
DW - day of week (from 0 to 6) (0=Sunday)
-----------------------------------
When you done press CTRL+D, that save task
